fields.about: Experienced cardiologist with over 15 years of practice in Damascus. Specialized in interventional cardiology and preventive heart care. Fluent in Arabic and English.
fields.education:
MD in Cardiology - Damascus University (2008)
Residency in Internal Medicine - Al-Mouwasat University Hospital (2009-2012)
Fellowship in Interventional Cardiology - American University of Beirut (2013-2015)

fields.about: Dedicated pediatrician with expertise in child development and immunology. Committed to providing compassionate care for children from birth through adolescence.
fields.education:
MD in Pediatrics - Damascus University (2010)
Residency in Pediatrics - Children's Hospital Damascus (2011-2014)
Specialization in Pediatric Immunology - Cairo University (2015-2016)

fields.about: Skilled orthopedic surgeon specializing in sports medicine and joint replacement. Experienced in both traditional and minimally invasive surgical techniques.
fields.education:
MD in Orthopedic Surgery - Damascus University (2009)
Residency in Orthopedics - Al-Assad University Hospital (2010-2013)
Fellowship in Sports Medicine - Jordan University Hospital (2014-2015)
